 Hari beats Topalov
Bilbao: Indias P. Harikrishna thrashed former world champion Veselin Topalov 1.5-0.5 to jump into joint second spot after the fourth round of the Bilbao Blindfold Chess World Cup. This was an excellent comeback by Hari  after losing to Norways Magnus Carlsen who won one game and drew the other to reach five points. GM Bu Xiangzhi, the lowest ranked player in the six-player double round-robin event, emerged sole leader on 8 points after beating Carlsen 1.5-0.5. Three points or one victory behind Xinagzhi are Carlsen, Harikrishna and GM Sergey Karjakin of Ukraine.  (PTI) 
